about.summary: Python API for Federal Reserve Economic Data (FRED) from St. Louis Fed

name: fredapi
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "fredapi" %}
{% set version = "0.4.2" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 753eb21fd75b461d36177eb9da298d1e0ec3ccfd4f64e13e74ffc216a89a2b96

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv "

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - pandas
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - fredapi

about:
  home: https://github.com/mortada/fredapi
  license: Apache 2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Python API for Federal Reserve Economic Data (FRED) from St. Louis Fed

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - tk3369
